The City of Baltimore's Foreign-Trade Zone, FTZ #74 was established in 1982 and has been continually expanded and modified due to various requests for additional space. Zone space, originally 60,000 square feet, currently contains more than 1,200 acres at multiple sites within the City of Baltimore, Anne Arundel, Baltimore, Cecil and Harford counties.

The Maritime Industrial Overlay District is designed to ensure the preservation of limited deepwater frontage of the Port of Baltimore for maritime use.
